  "description": "Sylvia Wynter's analytical framework — the overrepresentation of Man as if it were the human, the genre of the human, the colonial-racial constitution of the modern subject, and the demand for a new science of the human — for understanding how the modern Western subject became the implicit standard against which all other ways of being human are measured and found wanting.",
